The paper discusses the design of wireless-connected robotic networks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also focuses on communication and networking among robots, which suggests the sub-category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The proposed framework involves motion planning and cognitive radio, which falls under the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of artificial intelligence in the proposed framework, which suggests the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the need for consensus and cooperation among robots, which suggests the sub-category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
